Metro Pacific, PLDT, PNOC Exploration: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-05-10T00:56:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/metro-pacific-pldt-pnoc-exploration-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close,
unless stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 38.08, or 0.9
percent, to 4,257.15.  Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  : The owner of the
operator of the longest Philippine toll road’s first-quarter net
income rose to 820 million pesos ($19 million) from 650 million
pesos in the same period last year, driven by earnings from its
water and electricity businesses, it said in a statement
yesterday. The stock was unchanged at 3.52 pesos.  PLDT Communications and Energy Ventures Inc. (PCEV)  : The
company that owns shares in  Manila  Electric Co. said first-
quarter profit fell to 213 million pesos from 458 million pesos
a year earlier. The stock advanced 1.7 percent to 5.90 pesos.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  : First-
quarter profit at the country’s most valuable company by market
value was “better than expected,” Chairman Manuel Pangilinan
told reporters in Manila yesterday. The results are scheduled to
be released today. The stock increased 2.5 percent to 2,406
pesos.  PNOC Exploration Corp. (PECB)  : The state-owned oil and
gas company said ATR Kim Eng Financial Corp., Citigroup Inc.,
Deutsche Bank AG and UBS AG were shortlisted to bid for a deal
to be the company’s financial adviser for a planned share sale,
it said in a disclosure to the stock exchange. The stock dropped
5.8 percent to 65 pesos on May 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
